about.summary: Easily talk to Google's 'BigQuery' database from R.

name: r-bigrquery
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "1.3.1" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-bigrquery
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/bigrquery_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/bigrquery/bigrquery_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 9ea556bb2329dcffec96b7008855733e5b8e3135cdef4edbb07ed2b2b11e0057

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}              # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_c') }}        # [win]
    - {{ compiler('cxx') }}            # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_cxx') }}      # [win]
    - {{ posix }}filesystem        # [win]
    - {{ posix }}make
    - {{ posix }}sed               # [win]
    - {{ posix }}coreutils         # [win]
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-dbi
    - r-rcpp
    - r-assertthat
    - r-bit64
    - r-curl
    - r-gargle >=0.3.0
    - r-glue >=1.3.0
    - r-httr
    - r-jsonlite
    - r-prettyunits
    - r-progress
    - r-rapidjsonr
    - r-rlang
    - r-tibble
  run:
    - r-base
    - {{ native }}gcc-libs         # [win]
    - r-dbi
    - r-rcpp
    - r-assertthat
    - r-bit64
    - r-curl
    - r-gargle >=0.3.0
    - r-glue >=1.3.0
    - r-httr
    - r-jsonlite
    - r-prettyunits
    - r-progress
    - r-rapidjsonr
    - r-rlang
    - r-tibble

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('bigrquery')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('bigrquery')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/rstats-db/bigrquery
  license: GPL-3
  summary: Easily talk to Google's 'BigQuery' database from R.
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - adrianzo
